<br>
The bottom line was that until Luclin there was *no* need to use casters.  Absolutely none.  In a few encounters a Wizard might be useful, might.  But it was by no means required and melée did rule the game.  It was a completely melée game for over 2 years.<br>
<br>
Now Verant added two mobs that need casters, well, it doesn't change the game for most Guilds.  If a guild is still at the Dain stage, it's not for lack of casters, its for lack of Defensive, high HP Warriors, Clerics with clicker and the ability to switch between Defensive tanks and healer Focus as each Warrior loses Defensive.  Adding casters is going to do fuck all for them, they also won't ever get to Emporer Shreazza stage if they are currently at the Dain stage due to membership churn.<br>
